Name: Refrigerator Cold Cut-out
Help: Desired cut-out temperature in coldest position/ set-point

Name: Refrigerator Warm Cut-out
Help: Desired cut-out temperature in warmest position/ set-point

Name: Refrigerator User Setpoint
Help: In case of knob (potentiometer) failure, this setting would bring the temperature set-point to a particular desired position, between the warmest and coldest set-points, which could be set as the percentage between warmest (0%) and coldest(100%) positions/ set-points

Name: Refrigerator Cold Differential
Help: If set, the display will show the temperature in Fahrenheit.

Name: Refrigerator Warm Differential
Help: Difference in the cut-in and cut-out temperartures at the warmest position (set-point)

Name: Fan stops on compressor cutout
Help: If this pamater is enabled , the Fan will stop when the compressor stops.

Name: Refrigerator Min Runtime
Help: To prevent the compressor from frequent cut-outs, this parameter would ensure that the  compressor runs for atleast the specified time. This parameter overrides the cut-out temperature.

Name: Super Cool Time
Help: Tip: Setting this parameter too high could lead to unneccessary deep temperatures."

Name: Refrigerator Error Runtime
Help:
"To prevent the compressor from frequent cut-ins, this parameter would ensure that the  compressor remains in idle state for atleast the specified time. This parameter overrides the cut-in temperatures.

Tip: Setting this parameter too high could lead to unneccessary warm temperatures.

Name: Refrigerator Error Stoptime
Help: To avoid long idle state of compressor, this parameter would set maximum stop time allowed, after which the compressor would start irrespective of cut-in temperature.

Name: Refrigerator Overtemp Alarm
Help: This parameter only becomes active in the unlikely event of temperature sensor failure, the compressor would run for specified fixed run time, to maintain safe temprature of the application.

Name: Refrigerator Undertemp Alarm
Help: This parameter only becomes active in the unlikely event of temperature sensor failure, the compressor would stop for specified fixed stop time, to maintain safe temprature of the application.

Name: Refrigerator Cold Overtemp Alarm
Help:
"
"
Warmest temperature allowed at the coldest set-point after which an alarm would be raised.

Name: Refrigerator Warm Overtemp Alarm
Help: Warmest temperature allowed at the warmest set-point after which an alarm would be raised.

Name: Refrigerator Cold Undertemp Alarm
Help: Coldest temperature allowed at the coldest set-point after which an alarm would be raised.

Name: Refrigerator Warm Undertemp Alarm
Help: Coldest temperature allowed at the warmest set-point after which an alarm would be raised.

Name: Refrigerator Alarm Delay
Help: Time delay to raise over or undertemperature alarm signal. It is not active at power up.

Name: Defrost method
Help:
"Selection of defrost method
1. No Defrost: Select this option if you don't need defrost functionality. If this option is selected, it will disable all defrost related parameters.

2. Start by Time, Stop by Cabinet temperature: Select this option, if you want to start defrost after fixed specified accumulated compressor run time intervals, and stop the defrost when the desired Cabinet temperature (measures by temperature/ cabinet sensor) is reached as set in the Defrost Terminate temperatur (DTT) parameter.

3. Start by Time, Stop by Evaporator temperature: Select this option, if you want to start defrost after fixed specified accumulated compressor run time intervals, and stop the defrost when the desired evaporator temperature (measures by evaporator sensor) is reached as set in the Defrost Terminate temperatur (DTT) parameter.

4. Start and Stop by Evaporator temperature: Select this option, if you want to start and stop the defrost based on evaporator temperature.

Name: Fan on during defrost
Help: Used in natural defrost method to accelerate the defrosting."

Name: Defrost Terminate Temperature
Help: Temperature at which the defrost session will be terminated.

Name: Minimum Defrost Time
Help: Minimum time limit defined for defrost duration

Name: Maximum Defrost Time
Help: Maximum time limit defined for defrost duration

Name: Minimum Defrost Interval
Help: Minimum time interval between two defrost sessions

Name: Fan Start Delay
Help: Time delay to start the fan after compressor cut-in

Name: Fan Stop Delay
Help: Time delay to stop the fan afer compressor cut-out

Name: Remote Lock at Defrost
Help: If set, the display will not change value during defrost. The lock time is specified by Remote display Locktime"."

Name: Refrigerator Remote Offset
Help: This parameter can be used to calibrate for sensor tolerances. It cancels the deviation caused by long lengths of sensor cable.

Name: Refrigerator Remote Deviation
Help: This parameter is used to compensate for bad sensor placement, to minimize the influence of the ambient temperature to the sensor.

Name: Refrigerator Remote sample time
Help: if RST parameter is set to zero, the temperature would be displayed immediately as it is read from the sensor.  If set to any other value for example 10, ETP R1 would sample the temperature every ten seconds and moving average of 20 samples would be calculated. So if there is a temperature change, the ETPR1 would take 20 multiplied by 10 seconds i.e., 200 Secs(Max) to reach the exact temperature.

Name: Refrigerator Remote Display Locktime
Help: To avoid temperature fluctuations to be visible to the user, you can lock the display to show the temperature before a defrost was started. Or you can let the display show the setpoint. This parameter specifies how long time, it should be locked.

Name: Alarm
Enum: 1:Control Refrigerator,2:Control Freezzer,3:Alarm High Temp Freezer,4:Alarm Low Temp REfrigerator,5:Alarm High Temp REfrigerator,6:Alarm Low Temp Freezer

Name: Panel Spindle Selection
Enum: 0:Panel,1:Panel+Spindle with Stop Function,2:Panel + Spindle without stop function

Name: Freezer Min Stoptime
Help: Minimum stop time of fan in order to avoid sudden ON/OFF of fan.

Name: Freezer Min Runtime
Help: Minimum run time of fan in order to avoid sudden ON/OFF of fan.

Name: Super freeze time
Help: This is the time at which compressor will run continously when the controller is set to superccoll/superfreeze mode. During this mode controller will run at lowest set point and will restore the original setpoint after expiry of supercool/freeze time expires.

Name: Freezer Alarm Delay
Help: This fan delay is to avoid circulating warm air from evaporator due to defrost seesion.
